  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "&#39;Tis midnight, and on Olive&#39;s brow The star is dimmed that lately shone; &#39;Tis midnight, in the garden now The suff&#39;ring Savior prays alone.",
    "v2": "&#39;Tis midnight, and from all removed Immanuel wrestles, lone, with fears; E&#39;en the disciple whom He loved Heeds not his Master&#39;s grief and tears.",
    "v3": "&#39;Tis midnight, from the heav&#39;nly plains Are borne the songs that angels know; Unheard by mortals are the strains That sweetly soothe the Savior&#39;s woe."
  },
